oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Family canoeing the Tennessee River
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of three adults, a baby, and a dog boating on the backwater (floodwater) of the Tennessee River in Saltillo. The boat is a dugout canoe. The woman in the center is Louise Reed.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Canoes; Rivers; Families; Dogs
